g aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 25, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bso1665702780119.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bso1665702780119.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bso1665702780119.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bso1665702780119\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Properties Inspector\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bso1665702780119__properties_inspector_20857\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Properties Inspector to view and edit the properties of the current object, or multiple objects.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bso1665702780119__p_d5207e1_d5208e1_d5209e1\">Depending on the object selected in the worksheet editor, the Properties Inspector may include the following tabs:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bso1665702780119__li_d2207e1_d2208e1_d2209e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Object</span>—object properties that declare object behavior.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bso1665702780119__li_d2210e1_d2211e1_d2212e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Doc</span>—comments, or instructions for using the object. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ipc1665702585697.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ipc1665702585697.html\" title=\"Use this property to provide comments or instructions for the selected development object. You can use the toolbar and standard Windows keyboard shortcuts to format the text, copy and paste, and undo and redo edits.\">Documentation</a>.\n                        </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bso1665702780119__p_d5210e1_d5211e1_d5212e1\">Properties in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Object</span> tab are categorized for easy navigation. You can click the category to collapse or expand its contents.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"bso1665702780119__fig_w2016ab1b7b9b1_w2017ab1b7b9_w2018ab1b7_w2019ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Properties Inspector for a DSP Component </figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Property Inspector\" class=\"image\" id=\"bso1665702780119__image_mzv_j5g_cgc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Property-Inspector.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bso1665702780119__topic_d2682e1_d2683e1_d2684e1_d2685e1_d2686e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d381179e101\">\n                        \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bso1665702780119__li_d2213e1_d2214e1_d2215e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xui1665702780196.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xui1665702780196.html\" title=\"You can edit object properties using the Properties Inspector.\">Edit Object Properties</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bso1665702780119__li_d2216e1_d2217e1_d2218e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wvb1665702780266.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wvb1665702780266.html\" title=\"Use the Property Inspector to set a property on multiple subobjects to the same value. This can be useful, for example, if you want to have several fields use the same data type or same widget type.\">Edit the Properties of Multiple Objects</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bso1665702780119__li_d2219e1_d2220e1_d2221e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gtt1665702780356.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gtt1665702780356.html\" title=\"You can sort items listed in the Uniface IDE by clicking the sort icon above the column header.\">Sort Objects and Properties</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bso1665702780119__li_d2222e1_d2223e1_d2224e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kdb1665702780441.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdb1665702780441.html\" title=\"You can resize the width of columns by clicking the triangle in column header, and setting the desired width.\">Resize Columns</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ckt1665702791811.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define Entity Interface</a><p>Use this form to define the Database Interface property of and entity, which defines its physical characteristics of in the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mxt1665702792020.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define Field Interface</a><p>Specify the value of the Database Interface property of a field, which specifies how the field is stored.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwb1665702792301.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define Field Syntax</a><p>Define the field syntax definitions for a field, which determine the format required for data entered in the field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bjh1665702792519.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define Field Layout</a><p>Define layout definitions for the current field, which specify the way data appears when it is displayed in the field. .</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526216\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526216\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Properties Inspector Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 25, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Properties Inspector Use the Properties Inspector to view and edit the properties of the current object, or multiple objects. Depending on the object selected in the worksheet editor, the Properties Inspector may include the following tabs: Object —object properties that declare object behavior. Doc —comments, or instructions for using the object. For more information, see Documentation . Properties in the Object tab are categorized for easy navigation. You can click the category to collapse or expand its contents. Figure 1. Properties Inspector for a DSP Component How to Edit Object Properties Edit the Properties of Multiple Objects Sort Objects and Properties Resize Columns Related Links Define Entity Interface Use this form to define the Database Interface property of and entity, which defines its physical characteristics of in the database. Define Field Interface Specify the value of the Database Interface property of a field, which specifies how the field is stored. Define Field Syntax Define the field syntax definitions for a field, which determine the format required for data entered in the field. Define Field Layout Define layout definitions for the current field, which specify the way data appears when it is displayed in the field. . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}